[3
Date: 12 Oct 2000
From: H. Larry Penning, MD <hlpenning@netscape.net>
Source: Online News <http://www.iol.co.za>, 12 Oct 2000 [edited

A total of 7 new cases of Bovine Spongiform Encephalopathy (BSE) or mad cow
disease have been discovered in France, 5 of which were detected as part of
a test program launched in June involving the examination of cows that die
in strange circumstances.
足-
H. Larry Penning, MD
