[4
Date: 18 Oct 2000
From: H. Larry Penning <hlpenning@netscape.com>
Source: Ananova [edited
<http://www.ananova.com/news/story/sm_88219.html>

A total of 9 new cases of BSE have been detected in western France, the
Agriculture Ministry said.
The new cases bring to 71 the number of cases of BSE detected in the
country since the beginning of the year. Some 31 cases were detected in
1999. The ailing animals and their herds were slaughtered in keeping with
French policy, the ministry said.
Officials have stepped up routine checks of herds throughout France as part
of a broadened plan to help root out the disease. New cases of the ailment
are expected to appear in France until 2002, 5 years after authorities took
stringent measures to prevent more outbreaks.
足-
H. Larry Penning, MD
<hlpenning@netscape.net>
